   <text>
      <body>
         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">3/11/85 ¶  ¶ Since some time do I owe you, dear Mr Buchanan, ¶ John Buchanan (1819-1898). ¶  ¶ an answer to your kind letter; ¶ Letter not found. ¶  ¶ the correspondence has grown quite over my head; ...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">85.11.03</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To John Buchanan</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">A644, Mitchell Library, State Library of New South Wales, Sydney.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">3/11/85</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Since some time do I owe you, dear Mr Buchanan,<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn0" n="1">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">John Buchanan (1819-1898).</seg>
                     </p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>an answer to your kind letter;<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn1" n="2">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Letter not found.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>the correspondence has grown quite over my head; indeed I often wished the day had 48 instead of 24 hours, or that life was to each of us twice as long as it is. This year the extrawork for the London Exhibition,<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn2" n="3">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Colonial and Indian Exhibition, London, 1886.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>New Guinea Exploration<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn3" n="4">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>M was<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>heavily<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>involved with<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>the<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>New Guinea expedition<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>organized by the Society<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>and<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>led by<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Henry<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Everill (see Pulsford<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>(1885)). He was also actively<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>engaged with arranging a supplementary grant of £500 from the<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Society towards a<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>British-funded<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>expedition led by<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Henry<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Forbes<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>(see,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>for example,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>M to E. Strickland, 10 October 1885).</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>and industrial culture<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn4" n="5">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>A new edition of M's<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Select extra-tropical plants readily eligible for industrial culture</seg>
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>(B85.12.03) was published in 1885.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>has been enormous.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Let me hope, after your many years toil you can enjoy on a fair competency and in serenity the rest of your life, which I hope will be to you a long and joyful one. Your help as a naturalist and artist will be very much missed in the Wellington Department.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn5" n="6">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>In June 1885 Buchanan retired as botanist and draughtsman of the Colonial Museum, Wellington.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Would you allow me, to ask you<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">privately</hi>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>the question, whether the Auckland and Campbell islands are permanently inhabited by any one; also whether on Macquarie and Emerald Island<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn6" n="7">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Southern Ocean, south of NZ.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>any landing can be effected, or if they have any safe harbours?</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Why I ask the question, and why I ask it in<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">confidence</hi>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>I will explain. As President of the Geographic Society here I have in<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">3 or 4 weeks</hi>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>to give my annual adress, in which I wish to refer to antarctic exploration also. If this question was much talked of, in all probability articles on the subject would appear in the local press,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">before</hi>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>I had even myself a chance of my saying here. It seems that my remarks in last years adress led to the appointment of Hooker, M'Klintock and Nares as an antarctic explorat. Committee.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn7" n="8">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>M's 1884 Presidential address to the Victorian Branch of the Royal Geographical Society of Australasia (B85.13.25) is generally seen as marking the start of a campaign for an Australian expedition to Antarctica. In his 1885 address (B87.05.03), delivered on 18 January 1886, he urged the colonization of Auckland and Campbell Islands 'with Macquarie Island as an outpost', as a preliminary to an assault on Antarctica itself. Meanwhile, the British Association for the Advancement of Science at its 1885 meeting, in response to a paper by Admiral Sir Erasmus Ommanney, set up a high-powered committee 'for the purpose of drawing attention to the desirability of further research in the Antarctic Regions'. See Home et al. (1992).</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Regardfully your</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd von Mueller.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">for any informat on the antarctic islands I shall be very grateful</p>
         </div>
      </body>
